        </p>
        <p class="font-bold" id="ExcludeShipping">
          <em>Why are certain products unavailable to ship to Internationally?</em>
        </p>
        <p>
          There are some products that are unavailable for International Delivery. This can be due to logistical limitations that prevent us from sending products outside of the US. This affects products such as our Yerba Mate Mist SPF 30 and our nail polish. If we cannot sell a product using International Delivery we will always show you on the product page.
        </p>
        <p class="font-bold">
          <em>Why is my tracking number not updating?</em>
        </p>
        <div>
          If the tracking has not updated, it might mean the package hasn’t yet been picked up.
        </div>
        <ul>
          <li>
            Orders are generally processed and shipped within 48 hours.
          </li>
          <li>
            Our daily pickups are generally towards the end of the day.
          </li>
          <li>
            Tracking information will be updated once the packages have been scanned into the system at the carrier’s distribution center.
          </li>
          <li>
            Please note that there is no visibility for USPS First Class packages. Tracking for these packages will generally show when it was picked up by USPS and when it was delivered.
          </li>
          <li>
            There is step by step tracking for USPS Priority packages, but the USPS site does not always update immediately.
          </li>
          <li>
            It may take up to 48 hours for tracking to display on the carrier’s site. There may be several days when it appears your package is not moving to its destination. This occurs when your package is on a long haul truck or on a train. The tracking of your package is only updated when it reaches the next distribution center. It can take several days for a truck or train to arrive its destination.
          </li>
          <li>
            If the tracking has updated and suddenly stopped, it might be caused by a delay (weather, traffic, etc.) and should resume within a day or so.
          </li>
